		  over-reliance on AI, and lack of interpretability still
		  persist, raising concerns about trust, fairness, and
		  ethical compliance of AI systems. This workshop addresses
		  these issues by promoting the same multidisciplinary
		  perspective that characterizes the creation of SAI systems,
		  integrating HCI, AI, Ethics and Laws, Software Engineering
		  (SE) and End-User Development (EUD). Through discussions
		  and knowledge exchange, participants will investigate the
		  components of human-AI interaction that characterize the
		  symbiotic relationship between the two parties in
		  decision-making scenarios (for example, in the medical
		  domain).},
