  urldate	= {2024-11-29},
  abstract	= {Abstract The rapid growth in interest in Artificial
		  Intelligence (AI) has been a significant driver of research
		  and business activities in recent years. This raises new
		  critical issues, particularly concerning interaction with
		  AI systems. This article first presents a survey that
		  identifies the primary issues addressed in Human-Centered
		  AI (HCAI), focusing on the interaction with AI systems. The
		  survey outcomes permit to clarify disciplines, concepts,
		  and terms around HCAI, solutions to design and evaluate
		  HCAI systems, and the emerging challenges; these are all
		  discussed with the aim of supporting researchers in
		  identifying more pertinent approaches to create HCAI
		  systems. Another main finding emerging from the survey is
		  the need to create Symbiotic AI (SAI) systems. Definitions
